1. UK hourly weather data (http://badc.nerc.ac.uk/data/ukmo-midas/WH_Table.html) for the two parameters: hourly 10-min wind speed and 
 hourly 10-min wind direction. 1950-2013.
 
2. UK Mean Wind Data (http://badc.nerc.ac.uk/data/ukmo-midas/WM_Table.html) for the parameter: hourly maximum 3-sec gust speed. 
 1950 - 2013.

The cleaning has involved correcting mistyped data entries and removing erroneous and duplicate data records. Nearly 4000 wind and gust records in the NERC BADC MIDAS data have been corrected. Three corrections have been made to homogenise the MIDAS UK station gust records. These corrections are: (1) The location of 282 MIDAS stations have been determined to 10m precision; (2) Gust data imputation has been performed to give complete 45-year hourly and daily maximum gust coverage at 282 stations; (3) The effective heights of the MIDAS 3-sec gust recordings have been standardised to 10m where possible.</gtr:description><gtr:id>B2A790FD-2D06-4A24-9CCA-545142569693</gtr:id><gtr:impact>These cleaned and homogenised data have contributed to the development of UK windstorm products which are being offered for licencing to the UK insurance industry. A contract for a leading provider of natural hazard data and modelling services to market and sell this product is nearing completion. This company also plans to develop derived products from our data.</gtr:impact><gtr:providedToOthers>false</gtr:providedToOthers><gtr:title>Cleaned and homogenised UK MIDAS wind and gust station data 1969-2013</gtr:title><gtr:type>Database/Collection of data</gtr:type></gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutput></gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications/><gtr:identifiers><gtr:identifier type="RCUK">NE/N004728/1</gtr:identifier></gtr:identifiers><gtr:healthCategories/><gtr:researchActivities/><gtr:researchSubjects><gtr:researchSubject><gtr:id>E4C03353-6311-43F9-9204-CFC2536D2017</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>10</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Atmospheric phys. &amp; chemistry</gtr:text></gtr:researchSubject><gtr:researchSubject><gtr:id>EE4457DB-92A3-44EA-8D5F-77013CC107E0</gtr:id><gtr:percentage>90</gtr:percentage><gtr:text>Climate &amp; Climate Change</gtr:text></gtr:researchSubject></gtr:researchSu